---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Editorial Policy | How CareCost Intelligence Creates and Reviews Content" description="Review the editorial standards behind CareCost Intelligence, including authorship, review, sourcing, corrections, and how we separate planning content from advertising.">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="pill">Who, how, and why</span>
      <h1>Editorial Policy</h1>
      <p class="note">Updated: Mar 2026. This page explains how CareCost Intelligence creates, reviews, and updates planning content for the estimator, state guides, and care-cost resources.</p>
      <div class="tag">Last updated: Mar 2026</div>
      <div class="editorial-meta">Maintained by CareCost Intelligence Editorial Team</div>
      <div class="chip-grid" style="margin-top: 12px;">
        <a class="chip" href="#who-creates-content">Who creates content</a>
        <a class="chip" href="#how-content-is-reviewed">How review works</a>
        <a class="chip" href="#how-we-source">How we source</a>
        <a class="chip" href="#independence">Independence</a>
        <a class="chip" href="#corrections">Corrections</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="who-creates-content">
    <div class="container grid-2">
      <div class="card">
        <h2>Who creates content</h2>
        <p>Content is planned, structured, and reviewed by the CareCost Intelligence Editorial Team. We focus on consumer-facing planning guidance for senior care cost decisions.</p>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li>Estimator support content.</li>
          <li>State and care-type planning guides.</li>
          <li>Decision checklists and quote-validation workflows.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h2>Why we publish</h2>
        <p>Our goal is to help families compare scenarios more clearly before they commit to provider calls, tours, contracts, or major budget decisions.</p>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li>Planning over hype.</li>
          <li>Clarity over complexity.</li>
          <li>Decision support over referral marketing.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="how-content-is-reviewed">
    <div class="container card">
      <h2>How content is reviewed</h2>
      <div class="grid-3">
        <div class="feature">
          <strong>Drafting</strong>
          <p class="note">Pages are written to answer a specific planning question or support a decision workflow.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <strong>Editorial review</strong>
          <p class="note">We review for clarity, consistency, responsible claims, and alignment with site methodology.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <strong>Maintenance</strong>
          <p class="note">High-impact pages are checked regularly and updated when policy, pricing context, or trust content changes.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="how-we-source">
    <div class="container grid-2">
      <div class="card">
        <h2>How we source information</h2>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li>Official state and federal regulatory resources.</li>
          <li>Publicly available planning references.</li>
          <li>Program and licensure pages for state-specific context.</li>
          <li>Internal modeling rules documented in our <a href="/methodology/">Methodology</a>.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h2>How we handle uncertainty</h2>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li>We present ranges instead of false precision.</li>
          <li>We encourage users to validate with local quotes.</li>
          <li>We avoid publishing unverified provider-level claims.</li>
          <li>We disclose planning limitations openly.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="independence">
    <div class="container card">
      <h2>Editorial independence and advertising</h2>
      <p>CareCost Intelligence is designed as an editorial and planning resource. Advertising, sponsorship, or future monetization should not determine the substance of guidance pages.</p>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>Planning content is created for user value first.</li>
        <li>Sponsored placements should be clearly labeled.</li>
        <li>Trust pages and policy pages remain content-first.</li>
        <li>Estimator inputs are not published as user-generated data.</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="controls" style="margin-top: 12px;">
        <a class="btn secondary" href="/advertising-disclosure/">Advertising disclosure</a>
        <a class="btn" href="/methodology/">Methodology</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="corrections">
    <div class="container card">
      <h2>Corrections and updates</h2>
      <p>If a material factual error, outdated reference, or broken planning claim is identified, we review it and update the page when needed.</p>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>Material corrections are reflected in <a href="/updates/">Updates &amp; Corrections</a>.</li>
        <li>Pages receive updated timestamps when significant changes are made.</li>
        <li>Readers can report issues through <a href="/contact/">Contact</a>.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
